TICKET 2A
Title: Setup change detection + fmt/validate in GitHub Actions (changed folders only)
Type: Task
Priority: High
Estimate: 4 hours
Sprint: Current
Description:
Create a GitHub Actions workflow that detects which env/ or modules/ folder was changed in a push or PR, and runs terraform fmt and terraform validate only on those changed folders. Skip everything else.
Why:
Currently there is no automated testing. When we add tests, we don't want to test ALL environments on every push — that's slow and wasteful. If someone edits env/dev, only env/dev should be tested.
What to do:

Create .github/workflows/terraform-tests.yml
Add detect-changes job that:

Compares current commit vs previous commit (push) or PR base vs head (PR)
Extracts changed folders under env/ and modules/
Outputs a JSON list like ["env/dev", "modules/vm"]


Add fmt-check job that:

Reads the changed folders list
Runs terraform fmt -check only on those folders
Fails if any folder has formatting issues


Add validate job that:

Runs terraform init -backend=false + terraform validate only on changed folders
Fails if any folder has invalid code



Acceptance Criteria:

 Workflow triggers on push to main/develop and on PRs to main
 detect-changes job correctly identifies which folders changed
 fmt-check runs ONLY on changed folders, not all
 validate runs ONLY on changed folders, not all
 If no env/ or modules/ files changed → jobs skip (no wasted time)
 Tested: edit env/dev → only env/dev is checked
 Tested: edit modules/vm → only modules/vm is checked
 Tested: edit README.md → no tests run (nothing relevant changed)
 PR raised and merged to main
